Exactly one expression per rule (except CUSTOM_RULE). Examples:
- AUTO_APPROVE_BY_TEAMS: { operatorType: "CONTAINS_ANY", operandLeft: { predefined: "MembershipTeamsOfIdentity" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { stringList: ["Team-A"] } } }
- AUTO_APPROVE_FOR_IDENTITY_TYPE: { operatorType: "IN", operandLeft: { predefined: "IdentityType" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { stringList: ["TEAM_ID", "IAM_ROLE"] } } }
- AUTO_APPROVE_ALL: { operatorType: "ASSIGN", operandLeft: { predefined: "AllowAll" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { booleanValue: true } } }

Exactly one expression per rule (except CUSTOM_RULE). Examples:
- AUTO_DENY_BY_TEAMS: { operatorType: "CONTAINS_ANY", operandLeft: { predefined: "MembershipTeamsOfIdentity" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { stringList: ["Team-X"] } } }
- AUTO_DENY_FOR_IDENTITY_TYPE: { operatorType: "IN", operandLeft: { predefined: "IdentityType" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { stringList: ["DATANET_DBUSER"] } } }
- AUTO_DENY_ALL: { operatorType: "ASSIGN", operandLeft: { predefined: "DenyAll" }, operandRight: { userdefined: { booleanValue: true } } }

ToolSpecification.description:
(MCP tool from slack-mcp) Add a new row to a Slack List. Optionally set initial cell values.
Use get_list_content first to find column IDs and types.
Value format in "value" depends on column type (same as update_list_record): text (plain string), number ("42"), date ("2026-03-20"), select (option IDs: "OptXXX"), user ("W0000000001"), checkbox ("true"/"false"), email, phone, vote, rating, attachment, channel.

