Sort: by relevance (default) or timestamp. Use sort + sort_dir to control ordering.
Scope: use "messages" to search only messages (faster, saves tokens), "files" for files only, or "all" (default) for both.
Pagination: response includes "page" (current) and "pages" (total). To get the next page, call again with page+1. Use "count" to control page size (default 20). When page >= pages, there are no more results.

Results include surrounding context (previous/next messages) and thread parent messages for reply matches, so you can understand the full conversation without additional API calls.

Example: { "query": "deployment in:#engineering", "count": 20 }
Recent first: { "query": "outage", "sort": "timestamp", "sort_dir": "desc" }
Messages only: { "query": "error", "scope": "messages" }
Next page: { "query": "error", "page": 2 }

